                  </hi>. I am a sailor, belonging to the <hi rend="italic">Martindale,</hi> lying in the London Dock. On the 1st of February I met the prisoner in the High<lb></lb>way—we walked, till we tame to an archway, and there stood talking—she said she wanted to go across the road for a necessary purpose—I felt for my tobacco-pouch, and it was gone—I had 17<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in it—I laid hold of her, and called for a policeman—he took her—the tobacco-pouch and money were found in the street—I could not have dropped it—I did not feel her take it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> He was along with some girls, and was drunk. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No—I had a little drink—I knew what I was doing.</p>
